                    <span>Much of this book is obvious - use of XSLT to to generate code files, how to consume sql metadata.  But the author does a GREAT job of presenting the information in useful context.  I recommend it.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A must-read for code generation folks</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
